# ================================================================================================
# GITIGNORE MAINTENANCE NOTES
# ================================================================================================
#
# IMPORTANT REMINDERS:
# 
# 1. SECURITY FIRST: Never commit:
#    - Environment files (.env*)
#    - API keys, tokens, or credentials
#    - Private keys or certificates
#    - User data or financial information
#    - Database files with real data
#
# 2. COMPLIANCE: For financial applications:
#    - Exclude all PII and financial data
#    - Exclude audit trails and compliance reports
#    - Exclude any files that could contain cardholder data
#
# 3. REGULAR REVIEW:
#    - Review this .gitignore monthly
#    - Add new patterns as the application evolves
#    - Ensure team members understand security implications
#
# 4. EMERGENCY PROCEDURES:
#    - If sensitive data is accidentally committed, contact security team immediately
#    - Use git-filter-branch or BFG Repo-Cleaner to remove from history
#    - Rotate any exposed credentials immediately
#
# 5. TEAM COORDINATION:
#    - Keep .env.example updated with new required variables
#    - Document any new exclusion patterns in team communications
#    - Ensure CI/CD systems have appropriate environment configurations
#
# ================================================================================================